                            <comment id="15296308" author="krummas" created="Mon, 23 May 2016 12:29:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;small nits;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;we used to remove the sstables from the &lt;tt&gt;sstableMap&lt;/tt&gt; that had disappeared from disk, pushed a small fix for that here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/krummas/cassandra/commits/paulo/11739&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/krummas/cassandra/commits/paulo/11739&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;we had &lt;tt&gt;@SuppressWarnings(&quot;resource&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt; on &lt;tt&gt;getAndReferenceSSTables&lt;/tt&gt; in 2.2+- it should probably stay on &lt;tt&gt;getActiveRepairedSSTableRefs&lt;/tt&gt; now&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;public synchronized Refs&amp;lt;SSTableReader&amp;gt; getActiveRepairedSSTableRefs(UUID cfId)&lt;/tt&gt; seems to have 1 space too little indentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
